By these things it beeing now manifest that the King is not prosecuting the Caus of God, and walking in subordination to God, but rather in opposition to the work of God, and to the Covenant, and cleaving to the enemies thereof;

according to the Declaration of Kirk and State of Edinburgh 13. of August 1650. wee disclaim all the sin and guilt of the King, and of his father's hous, both old and late, and declare wee cannot own him, nor his Interest in the state of the guard betwixt us and the enemie against them, (if the Lord will) wee are to hazard our Lives; And further for the remedie of what is past, and preventing of our own sin and danger of the work of God in this land; wee humbly offer to your Lordships, that, besides the repenting of, and humbling of your selvs for these things, your Lordships would bee pleased, according to the Act of the seventh of Sep: last, judging it necessarie securitie for the caus, that the King forsake counsels and Counsellors that hath been opposite thereunto, and according to the Act of Parlament, explaining the invitation which approve's thereof onely in this sens, hee performing satisfaction to the four demands, and according to the Act ratifying the Treatie, and putting him in the exercise of his power, with the like restrictions and conditions usual, and according to the Counsels of this Kingdom and Kirk, to consider that the King not having forsaken the Counsels, and companie of Malignants, but still cleaving to the same, notwithstanding all the endevors of Kirk and State to the contrarie; and not having performed the satisfaction promised by him in the Treatie, and not ruling according to the Counsels of the Kingdom; but forsaking the same to join with malignant Counsels and forces which hee was bound to abandon, whether this bee not such a breach of his condition, to perform the satisfaction promised, and such a discoverie, that hee hath not joined cordially, and heartily in the caus and Covenant, as give's good ground, not to entrust him with the exercise of his power, till such time as there shall bee convincing, and cleer evidences of a real change in him, and that your Lordships should take an effectual cours for preventing of the King's conjunction with the malignant partie, for the time to com, and for the trial of the late malignant design of his deserting the publick Counsels, and of all those who have had accession to it, and for disabling malignants, and who

have by the late actings discovered the deep hypocrisie, and mocking of God by a profession of repentance) till they bee out of capacitie to hurt the work and people of God.
